"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-06-07-noc-announces-date-to-celebrate-olympic-day\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Published  on  By  The Nigeria Olympic Committee, NOC, has announced that the annual Olympic Day celebration will be held on Saturday, June 29, 2024, across the country.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23, \"end\": 48, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nigeria Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 50, \"end\": 53, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999852481927398, \"rank\": 1.4708038123855124e-05, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The NOC disclosed this in a statement signed by its Public Relations Officer, Tony Nezianya, on Friday.\", \"from\": 171, \"to\": 274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 175, \"end\": 178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999852481927398, \"rank\": 1.4708038123855124e-05, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic Day is a global event that commemorates the birth of the modern Olympic Movement, founded by Pierre de Coubertin in 1894.\", \"from\": 276, \"to\": 409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 352, \"end\": 368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999800984071467, \"rank\": 1.9901988867127778e-05, \"text\": \"Olympic Movement\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 381, \"end\": 400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre de Coubertin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year's celebration holds special significance as it precedes the highly anticipated Paris 2024 Olympic Games, where Nigerian athletes will compete and inspire the world with their achievements.\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 532, \"end\": 540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9697541604627677, \"rank\": 0.031189182547904242, \"text\": \"Nigerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Olympic Day is a chance for people of all ages and abilities to experience the magic of the Olympic Games in their own communities,\\\" said Babatunde Popoola, the Secretary-General of the NOC.\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 798, \"end\": 801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999852481927398, \"rank\": 1.4708038123855124e-05, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's an ideal platform to highlight the benefits of physical activity and the Olympic values of excellence, friendship, and respect.\\\"\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 938, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The NOC has received positive responses from various states and stakeholders, and preparations are well underway for the nationwide celebration.\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 1084, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 944, \"end\": 947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999852481927398, \"rank\": 1.4708038123855124e-05, \"text\": \"NOC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"States such as Abia, Anambra, Bayelsa, Delta, Edo, Enugu, Ebonyi, Lagos, Kogi, Gombe, Jigawa, Kebbi, the Federal Capital Territory, Kano, Kwara, Taraba, Imo, Ondo, Plateau, Rivers, Nasarawa, and Osun have already indicated their plans to organize activities for the event.\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1358, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1116, \"end\": 1123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bayelsa_State\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.684018549727104e-44, \"text\": \"Bayelsa\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bayelsa_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bayelsa_State\"}, {\"begin\": 1144, \"end\": 1150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ebonyi_State\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.978119132563627e-65, \"text\": \"Ebonyi\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ebonyi_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ebonyi_State\"}, {\"begin\": 1152, \"end\": 1157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lagos_State\", \"score\": 0.9999994157098515, \"rank\": 5.842904539539084e-07, \"text\": \"Lagos\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lagos_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lagos_State\"}, {\"begin\": 1159, \"end\": 1163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kogi_State\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5717092590360298e-53, \"text\": \"Kogi\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kogi_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kogi_State\"}, {\"begin\": 1180, \"e